docs.title: Install by python-pip
docs.text:
If you are a user, It's very simple. use the pip 

pip install uel

docs.title: Install from sources
docs.text:
make
If you cached binary of UEL's extensions, You can using 
make install

docs.title: Running
docs.text:
Okay, Let's run uels!

To run uel codes is very esay!

uel run <filename>

docs.title: UEL's information
docs.text: UEL is UEL's developers to develop programming language

docs.title: What language to develop UEL?
docs.text: The first. Developers using Python to develop UEL. After, Developers using some Python extensions, Developers to develop UEL with Python, Cython, and C/C++, Now, We temporarily deprecated C++, Because c can most of UEL's work, Not using C++ for now, But if some parts of C can't do it or are too complicated, consider using C++

docs.title: What performance of UEL?
docs.text: The UEL's running performance maybe very low now, But we are planning on the optimizer, and JIT, We believe that one day UEL will perform faster than C/C++. Because we have a big plan, Runtime Analysis bytecode and optimize the codes of dynamic. We trust the UEL's performance will faster than C/C++ on future!
